WEBVTT

00:45.186 --> 00:56.100
to say that while I agree that things are very bad and the times are difficult, that they're not quite as bad as that, I'm referring to the singing.

00:58.123 --> 01:09.077
Now let me try to help you to understand this situation in which we do find ourselves and which led me to choose that particular hymn.

01:09.898 --> 01:13.042
It's a hymn that expresses the problem and the difficulty.

01:13.410 --> 01:19.698
but there is one to whom we can pray, and therefore we are not without hope and we are not cast down.

01:20.680 --> 01:32.395
But we must be alive and alert, we must quit ourselves as men, and we must, in particular, as I am going to try to show you, use our understanding.

01:33.537 --> 01:43.250
Now then, I am reading once more these verses which we have been examining for a number of Friday evenings in Paul's epistle to the Romans, chapter 11,

01:43.842 --> 01:47.286
Let me read again from verse 18 to the end of verse 22.

01:48.928 --> 01:58.258
Verse not thyself because or against the branches, but if thou burst, thou bearest not the root, but the root thee.

01:59.319 --> 02:03.484
Thou will say, then, the branches were broken off, that I might be grafting.

02:04.024 --> 02:10.391
Well, because of unbelief, they were broken off, and thou standest by faith.

02:11.292 --> 02:13.074
Be not high-minded, but fear.

02:13.922 --> 02:19.150
for if God spared not the natural branches, take heed lest he also spare not thee.

02:20.472 --> 02:39.340
Behold, therefore the goodness and severity of God, on them which fail of severity, but goodness, but toward thee, goodness, if thou continue in his goodness, otherwise thou also shall be cut off."

02:39.360 --> 02:43.186
Now, I've divided this statement, which really begins

02:43.874 --> 02:48.339
after verse 16 under four main headings.

02:48.980 --> 02:50.422
We've already dealt with three of them.

02:50.442 --> 02:53.986
We've expanded it, explained the meaning of the terms and so on.

02:54.947 --> 03:11.826
We've also dealt with what is the specific teaching conveyed here and in turn in the third place we dealt with a problem that arises in the minds of Christian people as they read this particular teaching, the problem which we

03:11.970 --> 03:27.346
dealt with last Friday night of outer reconcile with this passage seems to be saying on the surface with other statements already made by the greater puzzle in this epistle and in other places and other teachings in the New Testament very well.

03:27.927 --> 03:39.058
We come down to the fourth division which I've described as general application of all this to us, to ourselves and to our present situation.

03:39.650 --> 03:46.637
As we come to deal with this, there are one or two preliminary remarks that have anxious to make and feel constrained to make.

03:47.819 --> 03:53.705
The first is that this which we are now about to do is something which we should always do.

03:54.866 --> 03:58.169
In other words, we should always apply the truth.

04:00.192 --> 04:06.418
The Bible and its teaching are never to be approached in a detached or in a theoretical manner.

04:07.458 --> 04:11.022
Now that is, of course, the besetting sin of expositors.

04:11.963 --> 04:14.906
It is still more the besetting sin of historians.

04:16.548 --> 04:20.212
The danger always is to take a mechanical interest.

04:20.232 --> 04:26.318
And to forget application, you'll find this in many expositors.

04:27.179 --> 04:33.466
They are interested in the words and meanings and shades of meanings and arguments and disputations, and they tend to leave it at that.

04:33.486 --> 04:37.330
I know there is a case which can be made for the expositor as such.

04:37.602 --> 04:43.788
that there is all that he has called upon to do, and we don't look to him so much for application.

04:44.629 --> 04:56.181
But it is a danger, and one can become so involved in the mere mechanics that one entirely forgets and misses the object and the purpose of the whole statement.

04:57.222 --> 04:59.584
And exactly the same is true about historians.

05:00.265 --> 05:01.346
I've often noticed this.

05:02.848 --> 05:05.170
It's a very interesting thing and a very peculiar thing.

05:05.986 --> 05:08.630
and the thing against which we should all garner ourselves.

05:09.211 --> 05:29.642
I've noticed throughout the years that speaking generally, historians seem to have a strange capacity or propensity almost of being entirely uninfluenced by the very history about which they write and to which they give their lives in study.

05:29.983 --> 05:32.146
I mean by that I've known many men and some of them

05:32.226 --> 05:36.230
I have known very well indeed, who have been particularly interested in the 18th century.

05:36.851 --> 05:48.202
But I know some of these men, and I can say about them quite truthfully, that I have never known men who are further removed from the Methodist fathers of the 18th century in whom they are so interested.

05:49.043 --> 05:51.266
It's purely a kind of antiquarian interest.

05:52.106 --> 05:59.474
Now, that's a terrible thing, it seems to me, that we should approach truth, either in the form of didactic teaching

05:59.618 --> 06:07.851
or in the form of history or any other form without realizing that it is meant to speak to us, to do something for us.

06:07.871 --> 06:16.144
There is nothing against which we should guard ourselves so much as a mere detached academic and theoretical interest.

06:17.926 --> 06:19.889
It should always be a living interest.

06:21.392 --> 06:28.082
And that is why it is especially the part of the preacher, always to be applying the truth.

06:28.866 --> 06:31.489
I've never called myself a Bible lecturer for that reason.

06:32.490 --> 06:33.811
The Bible is to be preached.

06:34.832 --> 06:36.574
It's always to be applied.

06:38.776 --> 06:43.200
Now, the apostle you see here makes us say this very thing.

06:43.220 --> 06:57.554
Here, as I've been showing you, is dealing primarily with an actual fact of history which had taken place, that the Jews had rejected the gospel and were outside the church, outside the kingdom.

06:58.018 --> 07:00.101
Whereas the Gentiles have come in.

07:00.442 --> 07:03.627
Now, that's a pure fact of history.

07:03.647 --> 07:07.493
But the apostle, you see, can't merely handle this as a fact of history.

07:08.194 --> 07:11.819
He's concerned with the meaning of this, with the relevance of this.

07:11.839 --> 07:16.246
What this has got to say to the church, to the Gentile Christians who are in the church.

07:17.248 --> 07:22.496
He applies the very fact of history which he is reminding these people of.

07:22.856 --> 07:26.482
And that is the thing I say, which we must always be careful to do.

07:27.330 --> 07:34.660
There's a great deal of history in the Bible, but the history that is in the Bible is not only history.

07:35.742 --> 07:36.883
That's the important point.

07:37.945 --> 07:38.365
Why not?

07:39.467 --> 07:43.332
Why is it that the history of the Bible must never be regarded merely as history?

07:44.233 --> 07:53.586
The answer is that the Bible history is merely illustrative of great spiritual principles.

07:54.498 --> 07:57.282
And that is undoubtedly why it has been given to us.

07:58.204 --> 08:10.503
The business of the history is to illustrate the great teaching, the great fundamental and eternal principles of God's plan and purpose of salvation.

08:11.124 --> 08:15.210
It's not meant to be something in and of itself which you can therefore either take or leave.

08:15.510 --> 08:16.732
Now, there are many people who do this.

08:17.373 --> 08:23.122
There are many Christian people who ignore the historical portions of the Bible and they don't see such much value in it.

08:23.554 --> 08:29.523
It's still worse when you get a Christian who dismisses the whole of the Old Testament and feels that it's no longer relevant to you.

08:30.564 --> 08:36.432
Now, it's not really tendency, I'm warning you against and trying to safeguard you against falling into it.

08:37.874 --> 08:47.368
We must remember, therefore, that history in the Bible is simply one of the ways in which the great principles are taught.

08:48.790 --> 08:50.593
That's one great lesson.

08:50.853 --> 08:51.634
But here's another.

08:53.602 --> 09:04.717
We must pay attention to the history of the Bible because these principles which are taught, partly through history, are always permanent and eternal principles.

09:06.259 --> 09:09.984
That is why you see the Bible never dates.

09:10.004 --> 09:13.108
That's why it's never out of date, or putting it the other way around.

09:13.169 --> 09:18.396
That is why the Bible is always contemporary.

09:18.416 --> 09:23.122
Now you can read here of what God did with the children of Israel thousands of years ago.

09:25.570 --> 09:29.574
But the fact that it happens so long ago doesn't mean that it's got nothing to say to us.

09:29.814 --> 09:36.460
It has for this reason, that it's the same God who dealt with them as who deals with us, and he doesn't change.

09:37.421 --> 09:48.652
So the principles which are taught in the history of things which happen so long ago are as aprecable and as relevant and as true tonight as they have ever been.

09:51.414 --> 09:55.218
Very well then I say that we must always remember the past history

09:56.322 --> 10:10.779
and examples of what has happened to nations or to individuals, that these are but illustration of these great eternal truths and principles that God is always teaching his people.

10:12.441 --> 10:17.708
So that then becomes the way in which we should always read the Bible.

10:17.728 --> 10:22.834
When you come to it, you don't say, oh, well, in the Old Testament, of course, I've got the history of the Jews,

10:23.170 --> 10:33.167
Well, if one happens to be interested in history or interested in the Jews, it's profitable to read the history of the Jew as you read the history of the Romans or as you read secular history.

10:33.568 --> 10:39.078
If you happen to have that sort of mind, well, it's quite an interesting and entertaining thing to do to read history.

10:39.258 --> 10:45.529
Now, that's the way in which you must never approach the Bible or into the New Testament.

10:45.549 --> 10:48.434
You may feel and people often have felt and have said this.

10:49.858 --> 10:58.228
They say, I can't understand why we have all this in the gospels about the wrangling that took place between the Pharisees and our Lord.

10:58.328 --> 10:59.550
What's that got to do with us?

10:59.650 --> 11:07.640
These miserable wretched Pharisees and scribes and Sadducees and doctors of the law were always coming along and putting their Christians and so on.

11:07.840 --> 11:09.222
What's all that got to do with me?

11:11.404 --> 11:13.407
This, you see, is quite a common attitude.

11:13.447 --> 11:19.314
People say, what we want is the positive teaching of Jesus, and they wish we hadn't got all of this historical

11:19.714 --> 11:28.245
addition, which while it was quite true and it took place, of course, has got nothing to do with us because it happened nearly two thousand years ago.

11:29.587 --> 11:35.274
And that it's all therefore merely of some purely academic, historical or even antiquarian interest.

11:36.155 --> 11:44.506
Now, that I say is an attitude which we must have either at all costs, and it all applies to this passage that is before us.

11:45.067 --> 11:47.730
You may say, why are you taking all this time over this?

11:48.194 --> 11:50.017
It was an immediate problem then, of course.

11:50.458 --> 11:52.300
Here were the Jews and here were the Gentiles.

11:52.360 --> 11:53.322
The whole thing was new.

11:53.602 --> 11:54.524
It was a live issue.

11:54.744 --> 11:55.666
What's he got to do with us?

11:56.086 --> 12:04.419
Why spend all this time in 1965 on something that was very relevant 1900 years ago, but surely is of no interest today.

12:04.619 --> 12:06.883
Now I want to show you how terribly wrong there is.

12:08.866 --> 12:10.929
In other words, we read the Bible like this.

12:12.211 --> 12:16.658
When you read about the history of the Jews in the Old Testament,

12:17.730 --> 12:19.252
You should always read it in this way.

12:19.292 --> 12:21.475
You should say, I am the Jews.

12:22.457 --> 12:26.542
When you read about the Pharisees and scribe, you don't read it as if you're reading a book of history.

12:26.823 --> 12:29.186
You say, but I am the Pharisees and the scribes.

12:29.446 --> 12:30.468
This is speaking to me.

12:30.688 --> 12:32.651
What our Lord said to them, He's speaking to me.

12:34.033 --> 12:36.857
Now that's the only profitable way in which you read the Bible.

12:37.758 --> 12:44.968
If you once detach yourself and just regard it as purely academic, theoretical, external history, you're missing the whole point.

12:45.789 --> 12:46.610
You're turning

12:46.882 --> 12:58.314
the Bible into a textbook of history or into the account of some ancient philosophy and teaching, out of which you can pick things up if you like now and again and try to apply them as best you can, but it's all wrong.

12:59.455 --> 13:09.005
This is always contemporary because God remains the same and men remains the same and the relationships between God and men remain the same.

13:10.106 --> 13:13.970
So the principles taught in terms of this old history

13:14.434 --> 13:20.824
are as relevant and as live and as up to date tonight as they have ever been.

13:21.545 --> 13:24.189
Now, the Scripture itself puts that in these words.

13:25.031 --> 13:32.983
These things were written for our examples upon whom the ends of the world have come.

13:33.524 --> 13:42.258
I think, if I remember rightly, I read that very statement to you last Friday night, and it is the most important one which we must

13:42.658 --> 13:49.047
Never forget it's in one Corinthians 10, one Corinthians 10, 11.

13:49.107 --> 14:00.122
Now all these things happened unto them for ensembles and they are written for our admonition upon whom the ends of the world are come very well.

14:01.324 --> 14:11.378
That is by way of introduction to the application of this extraordinary statement which the Apostle makes here to the Gentiles of his day and generation.

14:11.458 --> 14:15.344
the application of all that to us at this present time.

14:15.805 --> 14:16.245
What is it?

14:17.768 --> 14:19.731
Well, I'd like to approach it like this.

14:20.151 --> 14:24.498
First of all, let us look at the general principles which are laid down.

14:26.261 --> 14:32.530
With respect to our situation today, there are certain general principles taught very clearly.

14:33.331 --> 14:34.053
Here is the first.

14:36.717 --> 14:40.242
There seems to be always a tendency

14:41.602 --> 14:55.415
in the church, or if you like, in God's people, in the olive tree, there always seems to be a tendency to decline and to fall away from the truth.

14:56.976 --> 15:07.506
This, of course, is because we are not yet perfect, because sanctification is a process, and because we are dull and slow of hearing.

15:08.888 --> 15:11.410
The great principles that stands out here is

15:11.682 --> 15:17.731
that obviously there is this tendency in God's people to fall away from the truth.

15:19.734 --> 15:22.899
I'll show you the great illustrations of this in history in a moment.

15:23.059 --> 15:26.925
But here it is, of course, of the surface in the case of the Jews.

15:26.945 --> 15:30.731
Now, I want to put a sentence to you, which I remember reading.

15:30.811 --> 15:35.218
It must be over 30 years ago, and I'm quoting the men who was

15:35.522 --> 15:42.831
about as far removed from being an evangelical Christian as a man could be, but he was a great thinker and an account observer, the late Dean Inge.

15:43.432 --> 15:45.995
He produced a little book on Protestantism.

15:46.195 --> 15:47.237
It was one of a series.

15:47.737 --> 15:49.680
I'll never forget the first sentence in that book.

15:50.100 --> 15:50.841
It was so true.

15:51.602 --> 15:52.964
He put it all in one phrase.

15:53.204 --> 15:57.409
He said, every institution tends to produce its opposite.

15:58.691 --> 16:01.074
Now, that's a very profound remark.

16:01.602 --> 16:05.668
a very perfect summary of the very thing I'm trying to say here.

16:05.868 --> 16:09.494
Every institution tends to produce its opposite.

16:10.054 --> 16:16.123
Now, he was writing on Protestantism and what he was able to show so cleverly in which I want to repeat tonight is this.

16:16.844 --> 16:23.133
By today Protestantism has become almost the exact opposite of what it was at its beginning in the 16th century.

16:24.315 --> 16:25.397
That's what he meant.

16:25.417 --> 16:26.498
Now, this is the trouble.

16:26.719 --> 16:27.480
Why does it arise?

16:27.540 --> 16:29.042
Well, it arises for this reason.

16:30.530 --> 16:36.918
And I know of no more fascinating subject in this, apart from anything else, for the mind and for our understandings.

16:38.600 --> 16:48.792
One of the greatest heights and struggles that ever goes on is the struggle between the Spirit and the form, the Spirit and the form.

16:49.674 --> 16:51.756
Now, the Spirit must have a form.

16:52.978 --> 16:55.020
That's why you have such a thing as the Christian Church.

16:55.721 --> 16:59.826
An idea must always take form if it is to be of any value.

17:00.258 --> 17:01.219
Now that's quite right.

17:01.680 --> 17:06.286
You must have a form to the Spirit, but there is always a tension between these two.

17:07.969 --> 17:20.026
There are always certain dangers that arise, and the biggest danger of all is that the form tends to cripple the Spirit.

17:20.046 --> 17:22.810
Oh, what a fight there has been.

17:22.830 --> 17:25.914
I don't think you can begin to understand church history.

17:26.555 --> 17:28.818
You can't understand the Bible unless

17:28.962 --> 17:33.288
You've got to clear in your mind this struggle and tension between form and spirit.

17:35.011 --> 17:36.072
You see, what happens is this.

17:37.434 --> 17:39.317
You've got to have, I say, a form.

17:39.597 --> 17:43.422
In other words, there must be a minimum of organization, otherwise you can't do anything.

17:44.163 --> 17:47.869
You can be a vague dreamer, but you want to influence, you won't help anybody.

17:48.770 --> 17:54.578
Every idea has got to take form in some sense or other, but the moment you give it a form,

17:54.818 --> 18:04.568
You've got an organization, you've started on your great problem, and the problem is how to prevent the organization from throttling and killing the spirit.

18:05.509 --> 18:08.452
That's the problem.

18:08.472 --> 18:18.502
Or if you like it in terms of the spirit and institutionalism, you remember that great phrase in the book of Ezekiel at the beginning about the spirit in the wheels.

18:19.943 --> 18:22.546
I'll never forget being in America in 1937.

18:22.658 --> 18:47.822
at the General Assembly of the Presbyterian Church, and a man gave an address, and he was going to tell us about some marvelous movement of the Spirit, which he said had been taking place, and he took as his text this term, the Spirit in the Wheels, and one was expecting something tremendous, but I'm not exaggerating, neither of my caricaturing what the men said, but what it really came to was this.

18:48.302 --> 18:52.146
He evidently had had some idea, but all we were told about was,

18:52.354 --> 18:58.082
How they'd taken an office, and what they'd paid for the furniture in the office.

18:58.102 --> 18:59.724
Nothing but sheer organization.

18:59.785 --> 19:01.787
In other words, it was all wheels and no spirit.

19:02.448 --> 19:04.231
And there was no movement and nothing had happened.

19:04.691 --> 19:07.556
And nothing has ever happened since in connection with what he was telling us about.

19:08.216 --> 19:10.540
Now that's the danger, the wheel and the spirit.

19:11.201 --> 19:12.042
You work that out.

19:12.162 --> 19:14.726
Prejos, I give you that as a text.

19:15.487 --> 19:18.932
Work that out, the spirit, the relationship between the spirit and the wheels.

19:19.512 --> 19:20.594
You must have the wheels.

19:20.962 --> 19:25.327
but God forbid that the wheels should put an end to the Spirit.

19:25.828 --> 19:28.171
Now, this is the thing that is so clear.

19:28.371 --> 19:41.807
The whole story of children of Israel illustrates this, this harmony, this institutionalizing, this organization which ultimately destroys the Spirit altogether.

19:42.348 --> 19:47.634
Now, it's a very subtle process, this, and it is sometimes a very slow one.

19:48.514 --> 19:51.518
But the fact that it is slow doesn't mean that it doesn't take place.

19:52.119 --> 19:53.361
But it's subtle and slow.

19:56.706 --> 19:58.068
It's almost imperceptible.

19:58.108 --> 19:59.029
You can't see it happening.

19:59.610 --> 20:03.636
And that is why the tragedy takes place so often in the history of the church.

20:04.558 --> 20:08.343
People only wake up to the fact that it has happened when it's too late to do anything about it.

20:09.305 --> 20:11.207
Of course, this happens in secular history as well.

20:11.588 --> 20:13.991
It happened in Germany just before the last war.

20:14.212 --> 20:15.794
There were many good things about Hitler.

20:16.034 --> 20:21.019
And that's why many Christian people were entirely persuaded by him.

20:21.039 --> 20:23.121
And they only realized what he was when it was too late.

20:23.702 --> 20:24.623
The thing is subtle.

20:24.643 --> 20:26.164
It's insinuating.

20:26.184 --> 20:34.773
Now, perhaps one of the clearest illustrations of all of this is the way in which the so-called higher critical movement came in last century.

20:36.394 --> 20:38.597
You see, here at the church, she was orthodox.

20:38.617 --> 20:44.082
Perhaps not as alive as she should be, but I don't know that she was fairly orthodox up until about 1830.

20:45.314 --> 20:52.244
But this teaching gradually came in from Germany and it began to insinuate in various colleges and so on in this country.

20:52.464 --> 20:55.769
Well, people began to say, well, what's this that's happening?

20:55.789 --> 20:57.051
Then they said, but it's all right.

20:57.692 --> 21:02.239
Instead of recognizing it at once and dealing with it, they said, oh, it'll work itself off.

21:02.279 --> 21:07.386
This is just young people and you know, they tend to do those sort of things when they'll get older, they'll shake it off and so on.

21:07.747 --> 21:10.150
Well, it went on and on like that.

21:10.390 --> 21:12.914
There was nothing big, nothing great, nothing obvious.

21:14.242 --> 21:20.908
But by the day, of course, it's become predominating and controlling, and the truth is having to fight for its life.

21:20.928 --> 21:23.511
That's the sort of thing to which I am referring.

21:24.512 --> 21:33.860
All this tendency of the force and that which cripples the spirit to come in in a very subtle and often in a slow and imperceptible manner.

21:33.961 --> 21:37.224
Now our Lord Himself, of course, has used this illustration.

21:37.684 --> 21:41.808
He has compared it to the action of a moth or the action of rust.

21:43.229 --> 21:44.050
Moth and rust

21:44.194 --> 21:45.155
Don't act suddenly.

21:45.495 --> 21:47.277
It's a very slow process.

21:48.198 --> 21:51.942
That's why you used to have those disasters on railways in the last century.

21:52.263 --> 21:58.169
You've read the accounts of an express train going over a bridge and suddenly the bridge collapses.

21:58.429 --> 21:59.971
They didn't know about these things then.

22:00.571 --> 22:03.074
Not only rust but these stresses and so on.

22:03.294 --> 22:04.295
It happens imperceptibly.

22:04.315 --> 22:06.698
There's nothing to be seen, but it's taking place.

22:07.639 --> 22:10.482
Suddenly the first thing you know is the collapse of the bridge.

22:10.946 --> 22:20.035
Now that's something that you see so clearly in the Bible and you see it as I say still more clearly perhaps in the subsequent history of the Christian Church.

22:20.655 --> 22:21.816
There's the first principle then.

22:22.317 --> 22:29.404
There is tendency that comes in to declension and all because of the conflict between form and spirit.

22:29.644 --> 22:40.434
Secondly, the cause of this decline is always because we forget first

22:41.218 --> 22:43.081
and original principles.

22:44.222 --> 22:46.425
That's always the cause of the trouble.

22:46.445 --> 22:52.313
It is always the direct result of forgetting an original principle.

22:53.395 --> 22:53.876
What do I mean?

22:54.076 --> 22:54.757
Well, I mean this.

22:55.157 --> 23:04.671
The principle is, as the pistol to the Romans assures more clearly perhaps than any other single pistol, is that you stand by faith and by faith alone.

23:06.072 --> 23:07.775
It's the great statement of this episode.

23:08.356 --> 23:10.098
Justification is by faith.

23:10.562 --> 23:12.785
And it has always been by faith only.

23:13.826 --> 23:27.783
It is all, we are saved by grace through faith that none of yourselves, or as I quoted to you last Friday, 19 Romans 4, 16, it is by grace that it might be of faith through the end that the promise might be sure to all the seed.

23:28.664 --> 23:33.310
In other words, that's the fundamental controlling principle.

23:33.330 --> 23:40.178
And when things went wrong with the Jews and when they go wrong in the church, it is always due to the forgetfulness of that

23:40.322 --> 23:54.562
First principle, this is an astounding thing, but it is nevertheless a fact that all the greatest problems in the world today are due to the forgetfulness of first principles.

23:54.582 --> 23:59.689
Not some complicated involved outworking of the principle, it is always the first principle.

24:00.570 --> 24:03.314
Isn't that the whole problem of humanity today?

24:04.002 --> 24:10.913
You get all these conditions of inquiries and this and that can proposal, but the whole trouble is due to certain first principles.

24:10.933 --> 24:17.924
Indeed, there's only one, and that is, they don't realize that man is a sinner, and because he's a sinner, he will go on behaving as he does.

24:18.265 --> 24:21.069
They can bring in new institutions, they can do this and that.

24:21.089 --> 24:22.211
The problem will remain.

24:22.251 --> 24:24.575
They don't know their first principles.

24:24.996 --> 24:26.578
Now, it's exactly the same with the church.

24:27.490 --> 24:33.058
All the troubles in the church ultimately are due to the fact that we fall away from justification by faith only.

24:33.318 --> 24:36.963
We begin to take pride in the fact that we are Jews or pride in the fact that we are Gentiles.

24:37.263 --> 24:40.448
Our good deeds and works and our church and this and that, we've lost it.

24:41.950 --> 24:42.711
It's all a question.

24:42.911 --> 24:45.214
I'm losing a grip of the first principle.

24:46.616 --> 24:51.122
And then the third general principle that I find here is this one.

24:53.058 --> 25:09.379
that those who do fall away in that way from the truth and from the first principle are always the ones who persecute most bitterly those who still hold to the truth in the first principle.

25:11.322 --> 25:16.108
It was the Jews who put the Messiah to death.

25:17.189 --> 25:20.914
It was the Pharisees who were the ringleaders in that with the zenuses.

25:22.242 --> 25:33.836
It is always the men who have themselves lost sight of the first principle, who are the most bitter and violent opponents of men who still see it and who hold to it or have suddenly come to see it.

25:33.856 --> 25:48.914
And so the history of the church shows a constant repetition of what you get in the New Testament itself, that it is those who belong to the visible external olive tree, the external Israel

25:49.058 --> 25:55.647
are always the most better persecutors of the true Israel.

25:55.667 --> 25:58.070
It's as true today as it has always been.

25:58.350 --> 26:06.942
Now then, there I've put the principles which seem to me to be taught here and which are so relevant to our present situation.

26:07.402 --> 26:09.605
Let me go on then to my second big division.

26:11.588 --> 26:16.114
The second division is the lessons of history concerning these principles.

26:18.306 --> 26:20.109
In other words, the illustrations.

26:20.970 --> 26:22.171
See, that's what your Bible is.

26:22.472 --> 26:25.857
The Bible is a great book of doctrine and of truth.

26:26.157 --> 26:30.283
But it illustrates it in the case of individuals, in the case of nations, and so on.

26:30.623 --> 26:34.269
Now, the history is invaluable by way of illustration.

26:35.450 --> 26:43.362
And the supreme illustration of all of this, as I'm saying, the nation of the Jew.

26:43.382 --> 26:44.303
Oh, here it is.

26:45.124 --> 26:46.546
Standing out the forest.

26:48.386 --> 26:51.089
Surely it should be unmistakable, but alas, it isn't.

26:51.909 --> 26:54.952
You see, what we tend to do is that we look at the Jewish objectively.

26:55.493 --> 26:57.174
We don't see that it's applying to us.

26:57.535 --> 27:01.178
We condemn them, look back upon history and give our verdicts.

27:01.398 --> 27:03.981
We can't see that we are guilty of exactly the same thing so often.

27:04.541 --> 27:05.202
But there it is.

27:05.622 --> 27:08.705
It is the supreme example and illustration.

27:09.306 --> 27:11.949
These are the people who crucified their own messiah.

27:12.129 --> 27:15.152
He came into his own and his own received him not.

27:16.313 --> 27:17.714
There it is once and forever.

27:18.242 --> 27:20.285
But unfortunately, it didn't stop there.

27:21.326 --> 27:24.771
This has been repeated many times in the history of the church.

27:26.133 --> 27:35.466
There was at one time, you can read about them in the New Testament, a number of great churches in Asia, church at Ephesus, Laodicea and other churches.

27:35.766 --> 27:36.427
Where are they now?

27:37.549 --> 27:38.851
They've gone, they've disappeared.

27:39.532 --> 27:40.994
This very thing happened to them.

27:41.414 --> 27:46.962
These churches that were so privileged with the preaching of the Great Apostle Paul and others, John

27:47.170 --> 27:49.493
They've disappeared, they've just vanished.

27:51.695 --> 27:52.796
It was the same principle.

27:53.457 --> 27:57.381
You get the warning concerning that in the first three chapters of the book of Revelation.

27:58.502 --> 27:59.984
Or take the case of North Africa.

28:01.426 --> 28:05.050
Oh, they were great mighty churches at one time in North Africa.

28:05.070 --> 28:10.776
Never forget that the great St. Augustine was the bishop of Hippo in North Africa.

28:10.896 --> 28:12.678
Then there were other great churches.

28:13.118 --> 28:13.719
Where are they now?

28:13.739 --> 28:15.021
They've vanished, they've gone.

28:15.821 --> 28:16.402
Same thing.

28:17.794 --> 28:21.518
They went down for the same reason, ultimately, or indeed.

28:21.538 --> 28:27.205
It would be very simple to show that this tended to happen to the whole of the Christian church.

28:28.687 --> 28:33.212
I've referred to this on other occasions, so I'm not going to go into it in detail tonight.

28:33.272 --> 28:37.558
I've made references to it in my Campbell Morgan lecture back in last June.

28:39.780 --> 28:44.626
But if you try to discover how and why it was

28:44.866 --> 28:56.159
that the Christian church that you read of in the New Testament ever became the Roman Catholic Church of the Middle Ages, you will find that it's just this very thing to which I'm referring.

28:57.540 --> 29:05.689
The way in which it happened may be of interest, but it rarely can be put like this in a nutshell.

29:05.709 --> 29:13.618
It happened solely because they forgot this first principle, that justification is by faith only.

29:14.050 --> 29:17.898
that a man is not saved by his intellect, is understanding any modern by his works.

29:18.138 --> 29:32.146
But because a number of Greeks became converted, the man in the church at the instigation of the devil began to try to show that after all the Christian teachings were very similar to Greek philosophy at its best.

29:32.738 --> 29:33.659
It wasn't so different.

29:34.280 --> 29:40.386
They were persecuted, you see, and they were attacked, and they had to be apologized, and they tried to explain these things.

29:40.606 --> 29:46.432
And as they were doing it, they were leaving their great principle, not many wise, not many noble, not many mighty accord.

29:46.652 --> 29:49.374
They tried to show that they were noble, and that they were intellectual.

29:49.535 --> 29:51.096
They were denying the first principle.

29:53.138 --> 29:56.001
And the church became, in a sense, a kind of philosophic institution.

29:57.382 --> 30:01.106
I was reading strangely enough, only yesterday, an article by a modern

30:01.250 --> 30:16.813
scientist, who's the Christian, in which he was saying exactly the same thing, that the tragedy was that those men of the second century, in trying to deal with the Greek humanists of those age, gave their whole case away by becoming humanists themselves.

30:17.694 --> 30:31.154
And so the process went on, still more when Constantine brought the Roman Empire into the church, and the result is that you get something which, according to the phrase of meaning, is the exact opposite almost of the New Testament church.

30:31.906 --> 30:33.589
Think of the church of the New Testament.

30:33.829 --> 30:35.472
They haven't got buildings even.

30:35.492 --> 30:38.638
Our Lord would sit down in a boat and teach or sit on the side of a mountain.

30:39.339 --> 30:45.309
Contrast all that with all the pomp and ceremony and the ornate buildings of great cathedrals.

30:45.570 --> 30:49.296
St. Peter's in Rome or St. Paul's Cathedral in London or places like that.

30:50.098 --> 30:51.500
And Western's the chapel in a century.

30:51.520 --> 30:55.186
You see, everybody was imitating all that last century and they've gone astray.

30:55.387 --> 30:57.330
It's not primitive Christianity.

30:57.826 --> 31:01.450
It's all a forgetting of this fundamental, original principle.

31:01.651 --> 31:05.515
And it's happened almost in every conceivable section of the Christian Church.

31:06.536 --> 31:09.880
Think of Anglicanism at its beginning in the 16th century.

31:11.062 --> 31:13.104
It's clear of you about Rome and so on.

31:13.445 --> 31:15.827
Look at the prison, Anglican Church, and its tendency.

31:16.748 --> 31:21.394
Going back on almost everything that was done then, but still claiming to be the same thing.

31:22.242 --> 31:26.368
And it happens very slowly and in a very subtle manner, as I say throughout the centuries.

31:26.669 --> 31:28.311
It's equally true of non-conformity.

31:29.673 --> 31:31.877
Take Congregationalism, Independency.

31:33.078 --> 31:34.761
It started on that great principle.

31:35.222 --> 31:43.674
Now they are proposing to deal away with the Congregational Union and to form what will be called the Congregational Church of Great Britain.

31:43.694 --> 31:47.961
It's the exact opposite of what was started in the 17th century.

31:48.341 --> 31:51.346
Every institution tends to produce its opposite.

31:51.810 --> 31:54.455
And we are seeing it happening before our very eyes.

31:55.236 --> 31:57.039
You can see it equally clearly in Methodism.

31:58.342 --> 32:03.391
One wonders what John Wesley would think and do if he could come back to modern Methodism.

32:04.212 --> 32:08.179
They are denying almost everything Eastern for, except the circuit system.

32:09.041 --> 32:11.986
Almost everything else, they have thrown long since overbought.

32:12.578 --> 32:23.331
Now, this, you see, is something, therefore, that you can see in all the great divisions every one of them turns itself or is turned unconsciously into the exact opposite of what it was at the beginning.

32:25.253 --> 32:30.439
And all this is, but I say, further illustration of what we see so clearly in the Bible.

32:30.699 --> 32:33.863
Look at the prophets of the Remind Israel of what she once was.

32:34.324 --> 32:36.306
When you were young, says the prophet.

32:36.386 --> 32:46.400
Oh, how I led you with the cards of a man and so on, and how ready you were to be led, how you were a young virgin as it were, but you've become just a prostitute.

32:47.121 --> 32:49.364
Isn't that what the prophets are saying?

32:49.384 --> 32:53.049
How beautiful Israel was, how wonderful at the beginning, but what she's become.

32:53.089 --> 32:56.154
That's the terrible thing, and it's happened to all these.

32:56.514 --> 32:59.498
I know this happened even in the case of places.

33:01.782 --> 33:04.946
Read of Geneva in the 16th century.

33:05.218 --> 33:07.101
And go and visit Geneva today.

33:08.583 --> 33:11.927
You'll find it very difficult to get an evangelical summon in Geneva today.

33:12.248 --> 33:12.888
Geneva!

33:16.333 --> 33:17.715
I could name you villages.

33:18.917 --> 33:25.045
Some of you read the early life of Harold Harris, Treverka, and Talgar in the days of Harold Harris.

33:25.325 --> 33:25.986
Go there now.

33:26.327 --> 33:29.191
I don't know of any more derelict districts in a spiritual sense.

33:29.671 --> 33:34.738
I lived and was brought up partly in a village called San Geithon where the great Daniel Rowlands preached.

33:35.330 --> 33:41.139
for over fifty years, fifty-five years after his extraordinary conversion in 1735.

33:41.860 --> 33:47.228
But when I was brought up there, it was as dead spiritually as a priest could be.

33:47.288 --> 33:51.093
I have no recollection of ever having heard the gospel truly preached there.

33:51.113 --> 33:59.706
We were religious, but we knew nothing about the fire and the life and the evangelism of that great and mighty men and all who worked with him.

34:00.347 --> 34:00.808
What happened?

34:00.848 --> 34:02.450
Well, it's the same thing, you see.

34:02.722 --> 34:11.172
It became the mecca to which everybody went, and it became proud, like the Jews, and it lost the spirit.

34:11.192 --> 34:14.115
It became a kind of show place, and the spirit had gone.

34:14.135 --> 34:15.537
A shell was left.

34:15.917 --> 34:18.260
The husk and the kernel had vanished.

34:20.302 --> 34:23.586
And so it is with so many other places that I could mention to you.

34:23.606 --> 34:27.090
Well, there are some of the great illustrations in history.

34:27.490 --> 34:33.658
trying to show you that what the apostle is saying here is a principle that has been operating throughout the centuries.

34:34.039 --> 34:35.260
Old Testament will ever since.

34:36.262 --> 34:41.328
And happening today before our very eyes, but the tragedy is that people don't see these things.

34:42.870 --> 34:51.121
Then another thing which seems to me to be shown here very clearly by the history is this, is what I would call the principle of delay.

34:51.141 --> 34:54.546
I emphasize this because

34:54.658 --> 34:58.243
failure to see this and to understand this as often confused people.

34:58.904 --> 35:08.318
We all seem to have a notion that the moment we do anything wrong or begin to go astray that God will immediately deal with us, but he doesn't do that.

35:09.639 --> 35:10.921
There's a principle of delay.

35:10.981 --> 35:15.087
Now, you get, let me give you some examples of what I mean.

35:15.488 --> 35:17.010
God doesn't always act immediately.

35:19.202 --> 35:27.254
I read at the beginning of Luke 13 these words, there were present at that season some that told him of the Galileans whose blood-piloted mingled with their sacrifices.

35:28.255 --> 35:35.486
And Jesus answering certain to them, suppose ye that these Galileans were sinners above all the Galileans because they suffered such things?

35:35.966 --> 35:40.613
I tell you name, but except you repent, you shall all likewise perish.

35:40.814 --> 35:42.155
You see, they were citing a case to them.

35:42.356 --> 35:43.217
What about these people?

35:43.517 --> 35:44.759
His answer is, what about you?

35:45.641 --> 35:46.642
He always does this?

35:47.266 --> 35:59.768
or those 18, upon whom the tower of Salome fellas, and slew them, think ye that they were sinners above all, men that dwelt in Jerusalem, I tell you nay, but except ye repent, ye shall all likewise perish.

36:00.830 --> 36:01.912
He speak also this parrot.

36:02.974 --> 36:07.602
A certain men are defigatory, planted in his vineyard, and he came and sought fruit thereon, and found none.

36:07.906 --> 36:17.602
Then said he entered the dresser of his vineyard, behold these three years I come seeking fruit on this fig tree and find none, cut it down, why comfort it the grail?

36:18.543 --> 36:31.304
And he answering said unto him, Lord, let it alone this year also, till I shall dig about it and dung it, and if it bear fruit well, and if not, then after that they shall cut it down.

36:31.324 --> 36:33.948
And he was teaching in one of the synagogues on the Sabbath.

36:34.048 --> 36:35.250
Now there's the great principle.

36:35.778 --> 36:37.000
He doesn't cut it down at once.

36:37.300 --> 36:39.183
He gives it another trial, waits three years.

36:39.523 --> 36:41.646
He's ready to listen to an argument brought forward.

36:41.887 --> 36:42.608
Let me try this.

36:43.549 --> 36:45.832
That's God's way, the principle of delay.

36:45.872 --> 36:58.770
Or take it, as it was shown, I should have thought very clearly in the portion which we read at the beginning at the end of Matthew 21, another parable of our Lord, about these wicked husband men.

36:59.650 --> 37:01.453
You notice the pint of the parable is this.

37:01.693 --> 37:08.224
Our Lord is there giving a complete summary of practically the whole of the Old Testament, the wicked husband men of the Jews.

37:09.907 --> 37:11.409
They have God's vineyard.

37:11.429 --> 37:14.054
He's given it to them to look after for him.

37:15.216 --> 37:18.261
But then he sends his servants to get the fruit and they kill them and murder them.

37:18.281 --> 37:19.663
That's how they treated all the prophets.

37:20.865 --> 37:22.067
And he goes on sending more.

37:22.087 --> 37:23.349
He doesn't immediately destroy them.

37:23.509 --> 37:25.312
No, no, he sends more than he sent before.

37:25.532 --> 37:26.514
They do the same to them.

37:27.266 --> 37:30.610
all the patients of God, all running through the Old Testament.

37:30.630 --> 37:32.472
He doesn't at once put an end to them.

37:32.712 --> 37:34.935
He's very patient and at last he sends his son.

37:34.975 --> 37:37.858
And they do the same to him.

37:38.839 --> 37:42.404
And it is then and only then that he takes it from them.

37:42.824 --> 37:51.594
And so our Lord sums it up by saying, therefore say unto you, the kingdom of God shall be taken from you and given to a nation, bringing forth the fruits thereof.

37:51.614 --> 37:54.738
That's the Christian church consisting mainly of Gentiles.

37:56.546 --> 38:06.155
But then there is perhaps a still more striking statement of it at the end of Matthew 23, our Lord's terrible denunciation of the Pharisees.

38:06.916 --> 38:21.950
Listen from verse 34 onwards, wherefore behold I send unto you prophets and wise men and scribes, and some of them ye shall kill and crucify, and some of them shall he scourge in your synagogues and persecute them from city to city.

38:22.131 --> 38:25.714
Listen, that upon you may come

38:26.050 --> 38:37.369
All the righteous blood shed upon the earth from the blood of righteous able unto the blood of Zacharias, the son of Barakas, whom he slew between the temple and the altar.

38:37.449 --> 38:42.557
Veryly I say unto you, all these things shall come upon this generation.

38:44.220 --> 38:49.689
God has been patiently waiting for these people, sending his messengers, giving them opportunities.

38:49.909 --> 38:52.914
He doesn't strike at once, but at last he does.

38:52.994 --> 38:57.740
And all comes as it were upon one particular generation.

38:58.722 --> 38:59.042
That's it.

38:59.883 --> 39:05.150
Or if you like it in the case of an individual, look at our Lord's patient treatment of Judas.

39:05.691 --> 39:06.592
He knew all about it.

39:07.153 --> 39:10.498
But he addresses him as friend, even to the very end.

39:11.699 --> 39:15.685
He keeps on waiting patiently in this way.

39:15.705 --> 39:22.674
And if you want something similar in the realm of history, is there anything more astonishing than God's patience

39:22.754 --> 39:25.116
with the Roman Catholic Church of the Middle Ages.

39:26.358 --> 39:42.334
How he tolerated it and allowed it to go on even for centuries, and it was only as it were at the Protestant Reformation that God acted, putting them on one side and producing again his own true church in a visible form in the Protestant Reformation.

39:43.335 --> 39:44.255
It's the same principle.

39:45.076 --> 39:50.802
Well now, then, let me come to the particular replication of all that to us at the present time.

39:51.426 --> 39:51.906
What is it?

39:51.926 --> 39:56.150
Well, it seems to me to be perfectly plain and clear.

39:56.170 --> 40:09.363
The whole trouble with the modern Ecumenical movement, non-Roman and Roman, is precisely this thing and nothing else.

40:10.744 --> 40:15.889
It is entirely due to this very principle that the apostle is putting here before us.

40:16.149 --> 40:16.630
What do I mean?

40:16.690 --> 40:17.891
Well, what I mean is this.

40:17.911 --> 40:19.993
What was the trouble with the Jews at our Lord's time?

40:20.193 --> 40:21.074
It was this, wasn't it?

40:21.378 --> 40:23.601
They said, we are the people of God.

40:24.141 --> 40:26.284
We are the lineal descendants of Abraham.

40:26.644 --> 40:27.745
We are Abraham's seed.

40:27.765 --> 40:28.947
We are Abraham's children.

40:29.247 --> 40:34.193
We come down in an unbroken line from Abraham to whom all the great promises were made.

40:34.473 --> 40:36.035
Therefore, we are saved.

40:36.095 --> 40:37.616
We are the people of God.

40:37.897 --> 40:38.718
We are all writers.

40:38.758 --> 40:42.402
We are who is this fellow that seems to suggest there's anything wrong with us.

40:43.723 --> 40:44.264
Wasn't that it?

40:47.087 --> 40:49.490
And that is precisely the position today.

40:51.490 --> 40:56.300
What is called Christendom is assumed to be the Christian church.

40:56.721 --> 40:57.001
Why?

40:57.041 --> 41:00.448
It's assumed to be of necessity, the church.

41:00.468 --> 41:00.729
Why?

41:01.029 --> 41:04.937
Well, simply because it is the lineal descendant.

41:05.238 --> 41:07.563
It's come down as an unbroken tradition.

41:09.066 --> 41:11.090
It's the same external organization.

41:11.746 --> 41:16.172
It has this long history coming down and broken until tonight.

41:16.412 --> 41:20.758
It's true of Roman Catholicism, which traces itself back to the original Christian church.

41:20.778 --> 41:25.244
It's true of Protestantism, tracing itself back to the reformers and so on.

41:25.445 --> 41:26.807
It's true of all the denominations.

41:27.007 --> 41:35.759
They are assuming that because they belong to this same organization, to this one unbroken tradition, that there are necessity Christians.

41:37.621 --> 41:41.106
The external organization is regarded as the church.

41:42.050 --> 41:45.734
The tradition is regarded as a guarantee that we're all right.

41:48.137 --> 41:51.641
There is no concern about the purity of the church.

41:51.661 --> 41:56.788
There seems to be no concern about the message of the church and the faith and the practice of the church.

41:58.109 --> 42:08.882
Because a man is a dignitary in the church, we'll then it's assumed that he must be a Christian, though he tells you in his sermons and in his books, quite plainly that he's not a Christian.

42:08.962 --> 42:14.069
It is still argued that he must be because he belongs to the church and it's very terrible to say that he's not a Christian.

42:14.770 --> 42:17.414
In other words, what makes him in a Christian is that he belongs to the church.

42:18.135 --> 42:19.417
Not what he believes any longer.

42:19.637 --> 42:21.700
You see, we've left the principle.

42:21.720 --> 42:23.883
It is no longer justification by faith only.

42:25.085 --> 42:26.767
You can deny the deity of Christ.

42:26.787 --> 42:27.969
You can deny the miracles.

42:28.249 --> 42:29.992
You can deny the attorney's sacrifice.

42:30.232 --> 42:31.975
You can deny the literal resurrection.

42:32.255 --> 42:37.042
You can deny all these things and the rebirth and justification by faith only.

42:37.314 --> 42:39.177
But still, you're regarded as a Christian what?

42:39.237 --> 42:42.542
Well, because you're a member of the church, and every member of the church is a Christian.

42:43.243 --> 42:44.304
Why is he a member of the church?

42:44.324 --> 42:45.066
He isn't a Christian.

42:45.767 --> 42:46.488
That's the argument.

42:46.888 --> 42:49.192
The organization has taken the place of the Spirit.

42:49.632 --> 42:51.195
Tradition has taken the place of truth.

42:51.595 --> 42:55.842
Men are no longer concerned in the truth which is believed or in a corresponding life.

42:57.544 --> 43:02.612
The original basis of what makes a church a church is entirely forgotten.

43:04.074 --> 43:06.898
And the assumption behind the humanical movement is

43:08.226 --> 43:31.698
that because of the historical and the external continuity of the organization, that it is of necessity the Church, I say that that was precisely the error and the sin of the nation of the Jew when they rejected their Messiah and which caused God to pluck them out of the olive tree.

43:32.482 --> 43:40.610
And, of course, they are approving the analogy still further today by persecuting those who are still holding to the original principle.

43:41.551 --> 43:52.482
They say that those of us who say things like this are not Christians because we are lacking in a Christian spirit, which means that you allow anything to be said and that you never criticize, that you always praise everybody, that you never negative.

43:52.783 --> 44:00.050
They are persecuting those who hold to the original principle as an apostate church has ever done.

44:00.130 --> 44:05.436
since the days when the nation of Israel herself became apostate.

44:05.456 --> 44:14.726
The modern ecumenical movement is an exact reproduction of the very thing that the apostle is dealing with in this section.

44:15.187 --> 44:16.408
Let me give you one other thought.

44:17.590 --> 44:25.138
I feel that here also, the whole question of children brought up in the church is acutely involved.

44:26.786 --> 44:37.762
because they of all people are encouraged to assume that they are Christians because they were sprinkled when they were children or because they've always been brought to church and have always been in the atmosphere.

44:37.942 --> 44:38.923
There were never anything else.

44:40.966 --> 44:42.609
I'm not saying that they are not Christians.

44:42.669 --> 44:51.922
There are so many of them saying, God, all I'm saying is this, that this tendency is greater in them than in anybody else.

44:52.450 --> 45:08.006
the danger of assuming that because you belong to the organization, that you are of necessity a Christian, the danger of forgetting the vital principle, which is notification by faith only, individual experience of God and of the rebirth.

45:08.027 --> 45:09.268
Think that out for yourselves.

45:09.588 --> 45:13.512
It's not as acute a problem as the ecumenical one, but it's a very rare problem.

45:15.595 --> 45:18.898
Very well then I say next, what is it that awaits us?

45:20.418 --> 45:22.740
And the answer is that no men can prophesy.

45:24.082 --> 45:41.100
Because of this principle of delay that I've been showing you, all I know is this, that there is a day coming, when the apostate church, however big and powerful she may be, will be cast out, will be spewed out of the mouth of God.

45:42.621 --> 45:47.026
You get the account of that in Revelations, chapter 17 and 18, it is coming.

45:47.298 --> 45:55.186
The great world church that we are hearing so much about is going to be spewed out as the apostate vile thing that it is.

45:57.068 --> 46:01.332
And the sons of God will stand out in the brightness of their glory.

46:01.833 --> 46:03.154
I don't know when.

46:03.174 --> 46:04.936
I can't prophesy what may happen.

46:05.216 --> 46:06.998
These tendencies may go on and on.

46:07.338 --> 46:09.020
There is this conflict, there is this hope.

46:09.320 --> 46:15.346
Something great and tremendous is going to happen amongst the Jews before that happens, but that will happen.

46:16.226 --> 46:21.155
There is ultimately going to be not only a sifting, but this retribution.

46:21.375 --> 46:24.501
The principle at the end of Matthew 23 is still working.

46:24.801 --> 46:25.242
Very well.

46:25.282 --> 46:26.945
My last word is this.

46:26.965 --> 46:29.950
What is the way of safety for us in the light of all these things?

46:30.651 --> 46:33.757
My first answer is never forget Romans 1122.

46:33.857 --> 46:38.886
That's the best advice I can give.

46:38.906 --> 46:41.170
Keep Romans 1122 before you.

46:41.762 --> 46:50.854
Behold therefore the goodness and severity of God on them which fell severity, but toward the goodness, if thou continue in his goodness, otherwise now all shall be cut off.

46:51.155 --> 46:51.716
What does it mean?

46:51.916 --> 46:54.640
It means the need of constant self-examination.

46:56.162 --> 46:58.986
Let him the thinketh, his tendeth take heedless before.

47:00.007 --> 47:02.671
Don't rely upon the fact that you sound in doctrine now.

47:03.031 --> 47:05.234
That's no guarantee that you'll be in a year's time.

47:06.114 --> 47:08.517
Be careful, rest in your correctness of doctrine.

47:08.738 --> 47:13.184
You may become heard in your spirit and make your doctrine of no value to you.

47:13.204 --> 47:14.766
Thank God for any gifts He has given you.

47:14.786 --> 47:16.449
Don't begin to rely upon them.

47:16.969 --> 47:20.414
Because if you do, what applies to you is 1 Corinthians 13.

47:20.695 --> 47:23.398
Though I speak with a tongue of men and angels and of not charity.

47:23.599 --> 47:26.122
Though I have faith that I could remove mountains and so on.

47:26.383 --> 47:28.646
Though I understand all mystery, it's no good.

47:29.086 --> 47:30.909
You're sounding brass, tinkling symbol.

47:31.249 --> 47:32.772
All your knowledge is of no value to you.

47:33.092 --> 47:34.514
You see how subtle this thing is.

47:35.202 --> 47:38.747
Self-examination, constant fear.

47:39.628 --> 47:46.537
Be not high-minded, but fear always realize this danger, always check yourself by the original principle.

47:47.258 --> 47:52.104
Less you should, in a very subtle and slow manner, be drifting away from it.

47:52.124 --> 47:53.486
The next thing I say is this.

47:54.287 --> 47:58.252
You and I are responsible only for ourselves and for our age.

47:59.333 --> 48:03.218
We are responsible for this, but we cannot legislate for the future.

48:04.226 --> 48:07.291
When I say things like this to some people, they say, all right, we agree with you.

48:07.311 --> 48:11.918
But if we do what you're saying, is it any guarantee that things will be all right in a hundred years' time?

48:12.158 --> 48:16.905
The answer is no, but I'm not responsible for what my grandchildren may do, neither are you.

48:17.766 --> 48:19.850
That you are responsible for what you do.

48:20.390 --> 48:22.534
Every man shall bear his own burdens.

48:23.075 --> 48:33.330
You cannot legislate for the future, but our business is to see always that the church is pure inner doctrine, pure inner practice, whatever the cost.

48:34.242 --> 48:36.144
But we can't guarantee that it's going to continue.

48:36.525 --> 48:41.050
The church has been so pure many times, but always this other principle seems to come in.

48:41.270 --> 48:46.777
They fall away from the original, but we are responsible for our own day and generation.

48:47.117 --> 49:01.394
And lastly, it seems to me quite inevitable that our duty is clear, that we have nothing to do with a church which is guilty of repeating

49:01.922 --> 49:07.388
the fatal error and sin of the Jewish nation.

49:07.408 --> 49:29.394
We have nothing to do with a church that is apostate, with a church that puts organization before the truth, tradition before the truth, which has forgotten the very being and existence of itself, the principle that has ever brought into being and has made it what it is, a church which has departed from that, is no longer a church.

49:30.914 --> 49:39.264
And for us to be associated with such a body is to partake of its sin and to be partly responsible for its apostasy.

49:40.186 --> 49:51.900
Well, my dear friends, there are some of the things which seem to me to be spoken so plainly and so clearly to us at this very moment by this amazing statement of the greater puzzle.

49:52.501 --> 49:56.466
In Romans 11 verses 16,

49:56.610 --> 49:57.651
to twenty-two.

49:57.831 --> 50:04.219
May God apply them to our minds and hearts and spirits and give us grace to be obedient.

50:04.560 --> 50:12.129
If he know these things, happy are we if he do them?

50:12.149 --> 50:12.750
Let us pray.

50:16.554 --> 50:19.378
O Lord, our God, we come back unto thee.

50:20.499 --> 50:22.221
We thank thee that we can do so.

50:23.743 --> 50:26.066
We are conscious of our own unworthiness.

50:26.946 --> 50:32.392
We see in ourselves these tendencies about which we have been speaking together.

50:32.432 --> 50:37.838
We know that we are what we are by thy grace and by that alone.

50:39.981 --> 50:50.292
O Lamb of God still keep me, plus to thy piercing sight, it is only there in safety and peace I can abide.

50:51.654 --> 50:55.378
What snares and furs around me

50:56.674 --> 51:05.748
what fears and lusts within, the grace that sought and found me, alone can keep me clean.

51:06.849 --> 51:13.599
Though, alone can keep us clean in doctrine and in practice.

51:13.619 --> 51:23.474
Lord bless thy word to us, write it deeply, we pray that our minds and hearts and consciences and wills, and all God,

51:23.938 --> 51:32.806
give us that spiritual courage to practice what we believe, to put into execution what we see in Thy Word.

51:33.947 --> 51:42.075
O Lord, look down upon us in pity and in compassion, and lead us on by Thy Spirit.

51:43.416 --> 51:48.801
We thank You that we know that the ultimate victory is certain and secure.

51:50.003 --> 51:53.746
Keep us faithful until that great

51:53.922 --> 51:57.026
and glorious and wonderful day shall dawn.

51:58.167 --> 52:22.194
And now may the grace of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ and the love of God and the fellowship and the communion of the Holy Spirit abide and continue with us, now this night, throughout the remainder of this hour short, uncertain earthly life and pilgrimage, and until we shall be safely

52:22.754 --> 52:24.728
in the glory of the lusty.

52:26.239 --> 52:26.642
Amen.

